make bed file (genomic interval for selecting RRBS reads)

I want to make a bed file of the form: chr5 1307797 1355000 chr26 4050032 4074672 chr9 15554860 15576308 chr13 18142 30536

representing the ~300 genes that are differentially expressed in the avi iso experiment. Then I want to filter my RRBS reads over this interval and do methylKit to look for differentially methylated genes among this set.

I have a file ncbi.csv which has transcript ids and genomic intervals. (this file was generated as part of a separate project to map SB clone ids onto ncbi ids)

This is an EXAMPLE of the intermediate output I want:

ncbi<-read.csv("ncbi.csv")
ncbi
library(dplyr)
ncbi%>%select(gene_id,chrloc,chrstart,chrstop)%>%
  mutate(start=chrstart)%>%
  mutate(stop=chrstop)

I would like to add 10kb upstream of the genomic interval, to capture potential promotor sites. Upstream will depend upon the strand of the gene. I dont have strand information specifically, but I have start and stop sites for mRNA, from which I can infer strand.

this code works to compute new intervals with 10kb upstream of gene start

ncbi%>%select(gene_id,chrloc,chrstart,chrstop)%>%
  mutate(start=ifelse(chrstart<chrstop,chrstart-10000,chrstart))%>%
  mutate(stop=ifelse(chrstart<chrstop,chrstop,chrstop-10000))

I would like to first make a dataframe similar to this, but for the genes of interest.

First I need to make a file vector of gene_ids

read.csv("resLFC_no_F02.csv")%>%filter(padj<.05)%>%select(gene,padj)->targets
targets

Now I need a list of NCBI gene NUMBERS (these are unique to each gene, while the symbols may map to many different species).

edit to add other desired terms.. THIS WORKS (takes several hours to run with full list of ~24000 sequence headers)

df<-annot
for (i in 1:length(df$tx_id)){
#for (i in 1:10){
  entrez_search(db="gene", term=paste0(df[i,1],"[ACCN]"))$ids[1]%>%entrez_summary(db="gene",id=.)->output
  df$gene_uid[i]<-output$uid
  df$gene_name[i]<-output$name
  df$description[i]<-output$description
  tempchrloc<-output$genomicinfo$chrloc
  df$chrloc[i]<-ifelse(is.null(tempchrloc), "NA", tempchrloc)
  tempchraccver<-output$genomicinfo$chraccver
  df$chraccver[i]<-ifelse(is.null(tempchraccver), "NA", tempchraccver)
  tempchrstart<-output$genomicinfo$chrstart
  df$chrstart[i]<-ifelse(is.null(tempchrstart), "NA", tempchrstart)
  tempchrstop<-output$genomicinfo$chrstop
  df$chrstop[i]<-ifelse(is.null(tempchrstop), "NA", tempchrstop)
  tempexoncount<-output$genomicinfo$exoncount
  df$exoncount[i]<-ifelse(is.null(tempexoncount), "NA", tempexoncount)
}
df
function (x, df1, df2, ncp, log = FALSE) 
{
    if (missing(ncp)) 
        .Call(C_df, x, df1, df2, log)
    else .Call(C_dnf, x, df1, df2, ncp, log)
}

Now use the previous algorithm to generate the desired intervals for the bed file (to compute new intervals with 10kb upstream of gene start). Samtools wont take a bedfile if the start is not less than the stop, so also have to convert all intervals to plus strand:

targets%>%left_join(df, by=(c("gene"="gene_id")))%>%select(-tx_id)%>%distinct()%>%
  select(gene,chrloc,chrstart,chrstop)%>%
  filter(chrloc!="NA")%>%
  mutate(start=ifelse(chrstart<chrstop,chrstart-10000,chrstop))%>%
  mutate(stop=ifelse(chrstart<chrstop,chrstop,chrstart+10000))

export a version for mapping methylation sites back to genes

targets%>%left_join(df, by=(c("gene"="gene_id")))%>%select(-tx_id)%>%distinct()%>%
  select(gene,chrloc,chrstart,chrstop)%>%
  filter(chrloc!="NA")%>%
  mutate(start=ifelse(chrstart<chrstop,chrstart-10000,chrstop))%>%
  mutate(stop=ifelse(chrstart<chrstop,chrstop,chrstart+10000))%>%
  mutate(chr=paste0("chr",chrloc))%>%
  select(gene,chr,start,stop)
